Besides these appearances, Frey also contributed music for several commercials, with his jingle for [[Canada Dry]] ginger ale evolving into the obscure Japanese ''[[Strange Weather (Glenn Frey album)|Strange Weather]]'' bonus track "Ain't It Love".{{cn|date=January 2016}}-->

==Personal life==
Frey was married twice. From 1983 to 1988, he was married to artist Janie Beggs. He married dancer and choreographer Cindy Millican in 1990. They had three children:  a daughter, Taylor, in 1991 and two sons, Deacon in 1993 and Otis in 2008 and remained together until his death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/glenn-frey-singer-and-songwriter-who-co-founded-the-eagles-the-biggest-selling-american-rock-band-of-a6821876.html|title=Glenn Frey: Singer and songwriter who co-founded the Eagles, the biggest-selling American rock band of all time|first=Pierre|last=Perrone|website=The Independent|date=January 20, 2016|access-date=September 18, 2016|archive-date=June 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617101625/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/glenn-frey-singer-and-songwriter-who-co-founded-the-eagles-the-biggest-selling-american-rock-band-of-a6821876.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2016/01/glenn-frey-children-wife-cindy-taylor-frey-deacon-otis-frey-son-daughter/|title=Glenn Frey's Children: The Music Legend's Family|first=Stephanie Dube|last=Dwilson|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 31, 2022|archive-date=January 31, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220131011157/https://heavy.com/entertainment/2016/01/glenn-frey-children-wife-cindy-taylor-frey-deacon-otis-frey-son-daughter/|url-status=live}}</ref> Deacon, following his father's death, toured with the surviving Eagles<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/2017/11/20/glenn-freys-son-deacon-joins-eagles-as-the-band-eyes-a-new-tour/|title=Glenn Frey's son Deacon joins Eagles as the band eyes a new tour|website=[[New York Daily News]] |date=November 20, 2017|access-date=April 21, 2018|archive-date=April 26, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240426030700/https://www.nydailynews.com/2017/11/20/glenn-freys-son-deacon-joins-eagles-as-the-band-eyes-a-new-tour/|url-status=live}}</ref> until he departed in 2022 in favor of a solo career. He rejoined the Eagles in 2023.<ref>{{cite web |last=Willman |first=Chris |date=April 6, 2022 |title=Deacon Frey Leaves the Eagles After Long Run Filling in for Father Glenn Frey |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/deacon-frey-eagles-leaves-glenn-tour-1235226808/ |access-date=April 8, 2022 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=April 8, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220408004625/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/deacon-frey-eagles-leaves-glenn-tour-1235226808/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Illness and death==
Frey was diagnosed with [[rheumatoid arthritis]] in 2000, which affected his joints.<ref name="Azoff">{{cite web|last1=Kenneally|first1=Tim|last2=Waxman|first2=Sharon|title=Glenn Frey's Medication Contributed to His Death, Manager Says|date=January 18, 2016|url=http://www.thewrap.com/glenn-freys-medication-played-a-part-in-his-death-manager-says/|publisher=thewrap.com|access-date=January 18, 2016|archive-date=January 19, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230119115449/https://www.thewrap.com/glenn-freys-medication-played-a-part-in-his-death-manager-says/|url-status=live}}</ref> The medication that he was prescribed to control the disease eventually led to [[colitis]] and [[pneumonia]].<ref name="Azoff"/> In November 2015, the Eagles announced they were postponing their appearance at the [[Kennedy Center Honors]] because Frey required surgery for intestinal problems and needed a lengthy recovery period.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Kreps|first1=Daniel|title=Eagles Postpone Kennedy Center Honors Due to Glenn Frey's Surgery|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/eagles-postpone-kennedy-center-honors-due-to-glenn-freys-surgery-20151107|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=November 7, 2015|access-date=August 29, 2017|archive-date=October 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030184945/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/eagles-postpone-kennedy-center-honors-due-to-glenn-freys-surgery-20151107|url-status=live}}</ref> Because of complications from pneumonia, he never had the surgery and was placed in a medically [[induced coma]] at [[Columbia University Irving Medical Center]]. Frey died there on January 18, 2016, at the age of 67, from complications of rheumatoid arthritis, acute [[ulcerative colitis]], and [[pneumonia]].<ref name="Smith"/><ref>{{Cite news|title=The Eagles' Glenn Frey dead at 67|publisher=CNN|date=January 18, 2016|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/01/18/entertainment/glenn-frey-obit-feat/|access-date=January 18, 2016|archive-date=May 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230521231607/https://edition.cnn.com/2016/01/18/entertainment/glenn-frey-obit-feat/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Morton|first=Victor|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2016/jan/18/glenn-frey-eagles-guitarist-dies-67/|title=Glenn Frey, Eagles guitarist, dies at 67|work=[[The Washington Times]]|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 18, 2016|archive-date=September 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922051653/http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2016/jan/18/glenn-frey-eagles-guitarist-dies-67/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=<!--Not stated-->|url=http://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2016/01/18/founding-member-of-eagles-glenn-frey-dies-at-67-bands-website-rep-report/|title=Founding Member Of Eagles Glenn Frey Dies At 67, Band's Website, Rep Report|work=[[CBS News]]|via=CBS Los Angeles|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 18, 2016|archive-date=February 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220205600/http://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2016/01/18/founding-member-of-eagles-glenn-frey-dies-at-67-bands-website-rep-report/|url-status=live}}</ref> Some medications for [[rheumatoid arthritis]] or [[ulcerative colitis]] are immune suppressants and can compromise the immune system's ability to fight off pneumonia.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kenneally|first1=Tim|title=Glenn Frey's Death: Rheumatoid Arthritis Medication Can Lead to 'Disaster,' Doctor Says|url=https://www.thewrap.com/glenn-freys-death-rheumatoid-arthritis-medication-can-lead-to-disaster-doctor-says/|website=The Wrap|date=January 20, 2016|access-date=November 5, 2017|archive-date=December 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208043548/https://www.thewrap.com/glenn-freys-death-rheumatoid-arthritis-medication-can-lead-to-disaster-doctor-says/|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2018, Frey's widow filed a suit against [[Mount Sinai Hospital (Manhattan)]] and [[Gastroenterology|gastroenterologist]] Steven Itzkowitz for the wrongful death of Frey.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/widow-of-glenn-frey-sues-hospital-over-husbands-death-20180118|title=Widow Of Glenn Frey Sues Hospital Over Husband's Death - Noise11.com|website=www.noise11.com|date=January 17, 2018|access-date=January 18, 2018|archive-date=February 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226160130/http://www.noise11.com/news/widow-of-glenn-frey-sues-hospital-over-husbands-death-20180118|url-status=live}}</ref>

Frey was publicly mourned by his friends, fellow musicians, and bandmates,<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.eagles.com/news/266763|title=It Is With The Heaviest of Hearts That We Announce...|publisher=Eagles|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 19, 2016|archive-date=November 8, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108133223/https://eagles.com/news/266763|url-status=dead}}</ref> including [[Don Henley]],<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Grow|first=Kory|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/don-henley-on-glenn-frey-he-changed-my-life-forever-20160118|title=Don Henley on Glenn Frey: 'He Changed My Life Forever'|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 19, 2016|archive-date=December 5, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205023540/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/don-henley-on-glenn-frey-he-changed-my-life-forever-20160118|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Randy Meisner]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Dillon|first=Nancy|title=Eagles bassist Randy Meisner sad he and the late Glenn Frey can't 'Take It to the Limit' one more time|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/eagles-randy-meisner-shocked-glenn-frey-died-67-article-1.2502052|work=Daily News|location=New York|date=January 19, 2016|access-date=January 20, 2016|archive-date=July 28, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230728135052/https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/eagles-randy-meisner-shocked-glenn-frey-died-67-article-1.2502052|url-status=live}}</ref> [[JD Souther]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Cashmere|first=Paul|author-link=Paul Cashmere|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/music-news-jd-souther-issues-statement-about-glenn-frey-20160120|title=Music News JD Souther Issues Statement About Glenn Frey|publisher=Noise11.com|date=January 20, 2016|access-date=January 20, 2016|archive-date=November 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105010113/https://www.noise11.com/news/music-news-jd-souther-issues-statement-about-glenn-frey-20160120|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Jack Tempchin]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cashmere|first1=Paul|title=Jack Tempchin Shares Thoughts About Glenn Frey|date=January 21, 2016|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/music-news-jack-tempchin-shares-thoughts-about-glenn-frey-20160121|publisher=noise11.com|access-date=January 21, 2016|archive-date=April 21, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421191004/http://www.noise11.com/news/music-news-jack-tempchin-shares-thoughts-about-glenn-frey-20160121|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Irving Azoff]],<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Waddell|first=Ray|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6844112/glenn-frey-dead-eagles-manager-irving-azoff|title=Eagles Manager Irving Azoff 'Heartbroken' Over Death of Glenn Frey: 'I Can't Believe He's Gone'|magazine=Billboard|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 19, 2016|archive-date=September 17, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210917070256/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6844112/glenn-frey-dead-eagles-manager-irving-azoff|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Linda Ronstadt]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Lewis|first=Randy|title=Linda Ronstadt, whose backing band was the hub for the Eagles, remembers Glenn Frey|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-glenn-frey-ronstadt-20160120-story.html|work=Los Angeles Times|date=January 19, 2016|access-date=January 20, 2016|archive-date=March 14, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230314162357/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-glenn-frey-ronstadt-20160120-story.html|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Don Felder]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ultimateclassicrock.com/don-felder-glenn-frey-tribute/|title=Don Felder Pays Tribute to Glenn Frey's 'Amazing Genius'|first=Nick|last=DeRiso|date=January 19, 2016|work=Ultimate Classic Rock|access-date=January 19, 2016|archive-date=June 8, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608112134/https://ultimateclassicrock.com/don-felder-glenn-frey-tribute/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Joe Walsh]],<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/joe-walsh-dedicates-show-glenn-frey-detroit-7415711/ Joe Walsh dedicates ‘entire show’ to Glenn Frey as ‘One Hell Of A Night Tour’ hits Detroit] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240606055229/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/joe-walsh-dedicates-show-glenn-frey-detroit-7415711/ |date=June 6, 2024}}</ref> and [[Bob Seger]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/bob-seger-on-glenn-frey-he-was-the-leader-of-the-eagles-20160118|title=Bob Seger on Glenn Frey: 'He Was the Leader of the Eagles'|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=January 18, 2016|access-date=January 19, 2016|archive-date=November 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171125065038/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/bob-seger-on-glenn-frey-he-was-the-leader-of-the-eagles-20160118|url-status=live}}</ref> A life-sized statue of Frey was unveiled at the [[Standin' on the Corner Park]] in [[Winslow, Arizona]], on September 24, 2016, to honor his songwriting contributions to "[[Take It Easy]]". The song was the Eagles' first single in 1972, with Frey its lead vocalist.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.12news.com/news/local/arizona/winslow-gets-life-sized-statue-of-the-eagles-glenn-frey/326876266 | title=Winslow gets life-sized statue of the Eagles' Glenn Frey | date=September 28, 2016 | access-date=October 29, 2016 | via=12news.com | archive-date=February 2, 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202002324/http://www.12news.com/news/local/arizona/winslow-gets-life-sized-statue-of-the-eagles-glenn-frey/326876266 | url-status=dead }}</ref> At the [[58th Annual Grammy Awards]], the remaining members of the Eagles and [[Jackson Browne]] performed "Take It Easy" in his honor.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Rys |first=Dan |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/6875302/glenn-frey-eagles-tribute-grammys-2016 |title=Jackson Browne, Eagles Members Pay Tribute to Glenn Frey With 'Take It Easy' at the 2016 Grammys |magazine=Billboard |date=February 15, 2016 |access-date=February 16, 2016 |archive-date=October 28, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028184410/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/6875302/glenn-frey-eagles-tribute-grammys-2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> The road<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Glenn+Frey+Dr,+Royal+Oak,+MI+48067/@42.4945254,-83.1489741,18.13z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x8824cf5cbb5d8f19:0x56294c3c417c74e!8m2!3d42.4939192!4d-83.1479743|title=Glenn Frey Dr · Royal Oak, MI 48067|website=Glenn Frey Dr · Royal Oak, MI 48067|access-date=January 31, 2022|archive-date=January 31, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220131011127/https://www.google.com/maps/place/Glenn+Frey+Dr,+Royal+Oak,+MI+48067/@42.4945254,-83.1489741,18.13z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x8824cf5cbb5d8f19:0x56294c3c417c74e!8m2!3d42.4939192!4d-83.1479743|url-status=live}}</ref> running next to the high school (now a middle school) that Frey attended in Royal Oak, Michigan also bears his name.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wxyz.com/news/street-in-royal-oak-named-after-late-rock-star-glenn-frey|title=Street in Royal Oak named after late rock star Glenn Frey|date=February 19, 2016|website=wxyz.com|access-date=March 11, 2018|archive-date=May 10, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230510004223/https://www.wxyz.com/news/street-in-royal-oak-named-after-late-rock-star-glenn-frey|url-status=live}}</ref>

